org.svvrl.goal.core.aut

Class StateRun

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.StateRun
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<StateRun>, Run

    public class StateRun
extends java.lang.Object
implements Run, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<StateRun>
    A StateRun is a possibly infinite state sequence. A run is split into a finite prefix and an infinite suffix. If the run is finite, it has an empty suffix.
    Author:
    Ming-Hsien Tsai
